
@startuml

' Define classes and their relationships

class User {
    +String name
    +String email
}

class Student {
    +enroll()
    +makeRequest()
    +payForSession()
}

class Tutor {
    +String bankAccount
    +offerTutoring(subject: String, level: String, price: float)
    +setAvailability(availability: Availability)
    +confirmSession()
    +cancelSession()
    +scheduleFollowUp()
}

class Person {
    +register()
}

class Registration {
    +submitDetails(name: String, email: String)
}

class Subject {
    -String name
}

class Level {
    -String description  // e.g., primary, high school, university
}

class Availability {
    -Day day
    -TimeRange time
}

class Day {
    -String name  // e.g., Monday, Tuesday
}

class TimeRange {
    -Time startTime
    -Time endTime
}

class Time {
    -int hour
    -int minute
}

class TutoringOffer {
    +Subject subject
    +Level level
    +float hourlyPrice
    +Availability availability
}

class TutoringRequest {
    +Student student
    +Tutor tutor
    +Subject subject
    +Level level
    +DateTime proposedDateTime
}

class Session {
    +TutoringRequest request
    +DateTime confirmedDateTime
    +boolean cancelled
    +CancellationPolicy policy
    +followUpScheduled
}

class CancellationPolicy {
    +handleStudentCancellation(dateTime: DateTime)
    +handleTutorCancellation(dateTime: DateTime)
}

class Payment {
    +Student student
    +Tutor tutor
    +float amount
    +PaymentMethod method
}

enum PaymentMethod {
    CreditCard
    WireTransfer
}

class Award {
    +Month month
    +Subject subject
    +Tutor winner
}

class Month {
    -int number
}

' Inheritance and interfaces
User <|-- Student
User <|-- Tutor
Person <|-- Student
Person <|-- Tutor

TutoringOffer "1" *-- "many" Tutor
TutoringOffer "1" *-- "1" Subject
TutoringOffer "1" *-- "1" Level

TutoringRequest "1" *-- "1" TutoringOffer
TutoringRequest "1" *-- "1" Student
TutoringRequest "1" *-- "1" Tutor

Session "1" *-- "1" TutoringRequest
Session "1" *-- "1" CancellationPolicy

Payment "1" *-- "1" Session
Payment "1" *-- "1" Student
Payment "1" *-- "1" Tutor

Award "1" *-- "1" Tutor
Award "1" *-- "1" Subject
Award "1" *-- "1" Month

Tutor "1" *-- "many" Availability
Availability "1" *-- "1" Day
Availability "1" *-- "1" TimeRange
TimeRange "1" *-- "2" Time

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **Inheritance**: `Student` and `Tutor` both inherit from `User` and `Person`, since a user can be either a student or a tutor.
- **Aggregation/Composition**: 
  - A `Tutor` offers many `TutoringOffer`s.
  - A `TutoringRequest` refers to one `TutoringOffer`.
  - A `Session` is created from a `TutoringRequest`.
- **Association**:
  - A `TutoringOffer` has a `Subject`, `Level`, and `Hourly Price`.
  - `CancellationPolicy` is used by `Session` to enforce rules.
- **Enums and Value Objects**:
  - `PaymentMethod` is an enum.
  - `Time`, `TimeRange`, `Day`, etc., are value objects representing temporal data.

